# ============================================================================
# .dockerignore — Personal WAI-Illustrious ComfyUI RunPod Template
# ============================================================================
# Purpose: Keep Docker build context small and image clean.
# Only files actually used by the Dockerfile or copied at runtime should be sent.
#
# This fork deliberately excludes:
# - Git history and CI definitions (never needed inside container)
# - Personal snapshot / research data (.ignore/)
# - Local test mounts
# - Documentation that bloats the context tar
#
# The official base ships without a .dockerignore; adding one is a high-value
# first-step improvement for anyone forking for personal use.

# --- Version Control & Meta ---
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github/
CHANGELOG.md
LICENSE
*.md

# --- Personal / Research Data (explicitly never ship) ---
.ignore/

# --- Documentation (context only; not runtime) ---
docs/

# --- Build / Local Artifacts ---
*.tar.gz
*.tar
workspace/
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.venv/
.venv-cu128/

# --- IDE / OS Noise ---
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.log

# --- Scripts that are build-time only (we COPY specific ones explicitly) ---
# We do send scripts/prebake-manager-cache.py because Dockerfile COPYs it.
# fetch-hashes.sh is never copied into the image — no need to exclude explicitly.

# Safety: never accidentally include a previous ComfyUI checkout if someone
# runs docker build from inside a mounted workspace.
ComfyUI/
opt/
